SIMPLE: lunacy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lunacy
<hw>Lu"na*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Lunacies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[See
<er>Lunatic</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Insanity or madness; properly,
the kind of insanity which is broken by intervals of reason, -- formerly
supposed to be influenced by the changes of the moon; any form of
unsoundness of mind, except idiocy; mental derangement or
alienation.</def> <rj><au>Brande.</au> <au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Your kindred shuns your house⟦br⟧
As beaten hence by your strange <qex>lunacy</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A morbid suspension of good sense or judgment, as
through fanaticism.</def> <rj><au>Dr. H. More.</au></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Derangement; craziness; mania. See
<er>Insanity</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 875 --></p>

<p><ent>Lunar</ent>⟦br⟧
